content.en:
"This course is also designed to help graduate students develop skills required for conducting research on relevant topics. A research proposal should be handed in as a fulfillment of the course requirement at the end of the semester. To guide your work, you should:
(1) submit a research topic (i.e. research question(s)) on 6/1/2020;
(2) make an oral presentation on 6/15/2020, and hand in a complete version of research proposal on 6/22/2020. The final version of the proposal should include research questions, literature, hypotheses, and an outline of research design/method. (10 pages)."

